<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese Tourism Delegations Praise Cuban Social Justice </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0501021394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0501021394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We will be faithful in relaying to our membership 
the trust Cuban workers have in their leaders. This has been 
stated by the members of the first two Japanese delegations to 
visit Cuba as part of the Union Tourism program. They showed 
great respect and admiration for the attitude of the Cuban 
people in resisting and overcoming the U.S. blockade. The 
visitors belong to the provincial and municipal unions of the 
governments of (Tokaona), (Logano), (Tuyana), and Hiroshima and 
the public workers organization of Tokyo's administration. The 
Japanese delegations were received by Norma Ortega, secretary 
general of Cuba's Public Administration Union. The Japanese 
delegations made cash donations for the Cuban people. Both 
Japanese organizations showed interest in the current situation 
of Cuba, and stressed the advantage that it is to live under the 
social justice existing in Cuba. 

</TEXT>

