<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Upholds President's Right To Veto </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0401201894 Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 3 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PY0401201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion NOTICIAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Defense Minister Hugo Estigarribia stated: "If 
abusing the right to veto means resorting to this institutional 
tool as many times as is deemed convenient, then I think the 
executive branch is going to abuse it, but only to the extent 
that Congress, too, abuses its powers." 
  The secretary of state also noted that the military law is 
flagrantly unconstitutional, as is the Council of Magistrates 
Law and radio broadcasting law, and added that the veto is 
democracy's natural mechanism to submit a difference of criteria 
or legal interpretation to a third state power. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

