<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Official Criticizes Wasmosy, Successive Vetoes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0401214894 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 3 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PY0401214894 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Referring to reiterated comments by President 
Juan Carlos Wasmosy on the obstructive attitude of the 
legislative branch, Second Senate Vice President Basilio 
Nikiphoroff said: "The president of the Republic, through these 
new attacks, seems to be taking preliminary steps to close 
Congress." 
  During a recent visit to Alto Parana Department, President 
Wasmosy had stated that Congress seeks to hinder the democratic 
process and to affect the dignity and honor of the Armed Forces. 
  The National Encounter senator added: "Frankly I do not 
understand this criticism because Congress has expeditiously 
debated 90 percent of the draft bills in a coordinated manner 
and approved all the requests for credits submitted to us; I 
honestly do not understand this attitude." 
  Nikiphoroff also criticized the executive branch's 
successive 
vetoes considering that in six months it vetoed seven draft 
bills that had been approved by Congress. Nikiphoroff said: 
"The president vetoes everything; however, we are not doing the 
same." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

