<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Opponent Says Government Misjudges Current Process </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0401194894 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 3 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PY0401194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The persistent aggressive language used by some 
executive branch members against Congress reveals a lack of 
understanding of the process we are undergoing. This was stated 
by [National Encounter] Senator Diego Abente, who thus referred 
to the defense minister's comment that the president of the 
Republic will continue to make "abusive" use of his right to 
veto laws. 
  Sen. Abente said: "The veto is a constitutional tool that 
must be used moderately and with prudence. It may not be used 
only when the executive branch deems a draft bill 
unconstitutional." 
  Throughout history, this tool has been used in the world 
when 
the executive branch and congress' interpretations differ on how 
to solve a specific problem. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

