<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tribunal Announces Legislative Elections 1 May </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0401193494 Paris AFP in Spanish 0130 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0401193494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Quito, 1 Jan (AFP) -- On Saturday evening, 
Ecuador's Supreme Electoral Tribunal [TSE] announced that 
legislative elections will be held on 1 May to choose deputies, 
provincial councillors, and minority councilmen [concejales de 
minoria]. 
  In a resolution released via a radio and television network, 
the TSE stated that the call to elections abides by the 
constitution, electoral laws, and municipal regulations. "This 
call is based on the results of the fifth population census and 
the fourth housing census," the TSE explained, noting that 77 
deputies, 54 councillors, and 607 councilmen will be elected. 
The TSE added that the elections will last 10 hours and will be 
free and popular. Those elected will hold office for two years. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

