<H3> <TI>   Clashes Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0401195294 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1857 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0401195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1857 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Afternoon From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The situation in the State of Chiapas is as follows: 
  The Mexican Army currently controls the city of San 
Cristobal 
de Las Casas. Clashes that took place last night in the 
municipality of Ocosingo resulted in 27 guerrillas and two 
soldiers dead. The city of Altamirano remains under EZLN 
[Zapatista National Liberation Army] control while Army aircraft 
continue to overfly the region. According to the latest 
reports, the community of (Wisan) remains under guerrillas 
control. In addition, the rebels withdrew from (Otchuc) without 
Army intervention. 
  At least 2,000 additional soldiers arrived in Tuxtla 
Gutierrez which was already under control by the Army. In Las 
Margaritas, the Army entered to retake the city, but it had 
already been abandoned by the guerrillas. The community of 
Chanal was already abandoned voluntarily by the EZLN. 
  In concluding, the guerrillas announced they had mobilized 
in 
Venustiano Carranza and were present in other communities 
located along the Chiapas mountain range and the Guatemalan 
border. 

</TEXT>

