<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Planes Bomb Hill in Outskirts of Town </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0501013694 Paris AFP in Spanish 0031 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0501013694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, Mexico, 4 Jan (AFP) -- 
Three airplanes of the Mexican Air Force unexpectedly bombed a 
hill in the outskirts of San Cristobal de las Casas during a 
clash with members of the Zapatista National Liberation Army 
(EZLN) in a military spectacle that was watched by residents of 
San Juan de los Lagos neighborhood. 
  The residents climbed on rooftops and other high places to 
follow the actions of the three airplanes and a helicopter in 
this location where the presence of guerrillas had been unknown. 
  The rebels responded to the bombing with submachine-gun 
fire. 
The number of casualties is unknown. The action occurred about 
10 km from the center of San Cristobal, a town which the EZLN 
members maintained under their control on 1 January. 
  The battle site is alongside the highway linking San 
Cristobal with Ocosingo, toward which the guerrilla forces are 
reportedly pulling back after issuing a "declaration of war" 
against the Mexican Government and Army on 1 January. 

</TEXT>

