<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Town Under Civilian, Military Control </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0501021994 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0132 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0501021994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, 4 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- The 
Mexican Air Force launched today a brief operation in a 
mountainous area near this southeastern Chiapas city against 
armed groups dislodged from several towns, witnesses reported. 
  Local clergyman Gonzalo Ituarte Verduzco said that airplanes 
and a helicopter fired shots between 1700 and 1800 (2300 and 
0000 GMT) near El Corralito, southeast of San Cristobal de la 
Casas, and the armed groups responded from the ground. 
  San Cristobal de las Casas, one of the first cities seized 
on 
1 January and occupied the following day by armed men of the 
so-called Zapatista National Liberation Army, is under the 
control of civilian and military authorities. 
  The violent seizure of towns and Army attacks have left 96 
dead, including 59 members of the armed groups, 22 policemen, 
seven soldiers, and five civilians, according to official 
reports. 

</TEXT>

