<H3> <TI>   Guatemala Not To Permit Incursions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0501033194 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0130 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0501033194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Elisabeth Diaz Otero; from the "Vector 21" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Guatemala will not permit incursions by armed 
individuals into that territory, stated Guatemalan Ambassador to 
Mexico Alejandro Maldonado. He said that the patrolling of 
Guatemala's border with Chiapas is normal and that no one can 
cross the border illegally. 
  In leaving Los Pinos Residence, where Mexican President 
Carlos Salinas received new year greetings from the diplomatic 
corp accredited to Mexico, Maldonado said that Guatemala cannot 
cooperate with Mexico in resolving the armed conflict in 
northern Chiapas State. Let's hear what he had to say: 
  [Begin Maldonado recording] The Guatemalan Government has to 
protect its own borders, Guatemalan territory. Regarding 
cooperation, nothing has been said about that, and we do not 
think it is necessary, because we believe that the Mexican state 
has complete and absolute control over its actions. [end 
recording] 
  The diplomat denied that there are Guatemalans involved in 
the Chiapas conflict and that the problem there could extend 
beyond the border and become a regional problem. 

</TEXT>

