<H3> <TI>   Government Denies Guatemalan Participation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0501050894 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 0430 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0501050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 0430 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Evening from Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] In view of the developments in Chiapas State, the 
Foreign Relations Secretariat [SRE] issued a communique on the 
evening of 4 January that states the following: 
  Regarding the possible participation of Central American 
forces in the conflict in the four municipalities of Chiapas 
State, the SRE reports that, according to information available 
to the proper authorities, though foreign individuals may be 
participating, there are no signs that lead us to believe that 
there is an organizational [organica] participation by the 
Guatemalan National Revolutionary Unity [URNG]. 

