<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   URNG Communique Denies Ties to Mexican Rebels </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0601015094 Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO in Spanish 5 Jan 
94 p 42 </F>

<F P=103> PA0601015094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City SIGLO VEINTIUNO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Press communique" issued by the Guatemalan National </F>
Revolutionary Unity on 3 January; place not given] 
  [Text] In view of the events in Chiapas, the Guatemalan 
National Revolutionary Unity (URNG) wants to state that at no 
time has it participated in those events. It also vigorously and 
categorically denies reports irresponsibly disseminated by 
Guatemalan Army spokespersons trying to use this situation to 
implicate the URNG and create an unfavorable climate at a time 
when, under a call from the United Nations, preliminary peace 
talks will be resumed with the Guatemalan Government and Army in 
Mexico on 6 January. 
  The URNG has been, is, and will be respectful of Mexico's 
sovereignty. Therefore, our forces have no responsibility in 
these types of events. 
  [Signed] URNG 
  [Dated] 3 January 1994 

</TEXT>

