<H3> <TI>   Moscoso de Gruber Meets Endara, Views Possible Alliances </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0601154694 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0601154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Ciro Ortega; from the "RPC Television News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] Mireya Moscoso de Gruber, Arnulfist Party [PA] 
presidential hopeful, met this afternoon with President 
Guillermo Endara Galimany. They discussed the government 
alliance and its prospects for the presidential elections. PA 
members said their hopes to head the presidential ticket has 
strengthened. The issue of the alliance was discussed during a 
meeting held this afternoon at the Palace of the Herons between 
President Guillermo Endara Galimany and Mireya Moscoso de Gruber. 
  [Begin recording] [Moscoso de Gruber] We obviously talked 
about the government alliance. I told the president that the PA 
wants to maintain this alliance. I informed him we will soon 
talk to Molirena [Liberal Nationalist Republican Movement] so 
they decide whether they want to remain in this alliance with 
the PA or wish to abandon the alliance. 
  [Ortega] Would any other political group, such as 
Solidarity, 
join this alliance? 
  [Moscoso de Gruber] We have been talking to some parties. We 
have also spoken to Solidarity representatives, but I think they 
are waiting to see what will happen with the government 
alliance. So far we have only talked without reaching any 
special commitments. 
  [Ortega] It should be pointed out that [former Comptroller 
General] Ruben Dario Carles' presidential candidacy has been 
endorsed by Morena [National Renewal Movement]. To what degree 
does this pose an obstacle to your aspirations to be top leaders 
of the PA? 
  [Moscoso de Gruber] No, Morena has every right to nominate 
Mr. Carles for the presidency. We, the Arnulfists, are going to 
nominate our candidate on 23 January. It is no obstacle for us 
that Morena nominated Carles. 
  [Ortega] Finally, it has been learned some political parties 
have hidden weapons. How do Arnulfists view this? Do they feel 
threatened by this irregular situation? 
  [Moscoso de Gruber] It is regrettable that at this point it 
is said some political parties maintain weapons, which they will 
definitely use in the upcoming elections. It is regrettable 
they would try to disrupt peace in the next elections. We want 
the upcoming elections to be peaceful, although from what we 
said in April in the city of Boquete, I thought at that time 
that the next elections would not be peaceful. We believe 
Panamanians want peace, free elections, and to live in a 
democratic country. [end recording] 
  Mireya Moscoso de Gruber highlighted once more that she will 
not give up leading the presidential ticket. She also noted 
that once the campaign begins, her popularity and that of the PA 
will increase and the results of polls will change completely. 

</TEXT>

