<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senator Nelson Carneiro Joins Progressive Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0501175694 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 29 Dec 93 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PY0501175694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] After refusing to continue to fight for greater 
influence within the PMDB [Brazilian Democratic Movement Party], 
of which he was a founding member, Senator Nelson Carneiro 
yesterday joined the Progressive Party [PP]. According to PP 
sources, 200 other people have joined the PP, including 
Councilwoman Laura Carneiro, who is Senator Carneiro's daughter. 
Carneiro will be allowed to nominate 21 candidates for the PP 
ticket in Rio de Janeiro; that is, 15 candidates for state 
deputies, and six candidates for the Federal Chamber of 
Deputies. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

