<H3> <TI>   Socialist Party Rejects Pedro Collor's Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0601124894 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 0900 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0601124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Entrepreneur Pedro Collor will not join the PSB 
[Brazilian Socialist Party]. The party national executive board 
decided to cancel his membership after his name was rejected by 
eight regional party boards. 
  Former President Fernando Collor's brother has not yet 
decided on his possibly joining the PMN [National Mobilization 
Party]. 
  Pedro Collor, who pressed the charges that led to the 
creation of the CPI [Congressional Investigating Committee] that 
investigated entrepreneur Paulo Cesar Farias, said he will 
remain a member of the Alagoas Popular Leftist Front. The PSB 
supported this decision. 

</TEXT>

