<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rebels Reject Dialogue With Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0501153194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1432 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0501153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tuxtla Gutierrez (Mexico), 5 Jan (EFE) -- The 
Mexican Government today asked the rebel Zapatista National 
Liberation Army (EZLN) to establish a dialogue and end the armed 
struggle, but the guerrillas have refused. 
  Eloy Cantu Segovia, the sole spokesman for the Mexican 
Government in Chiapas, today reiterated the authorities' resolve 
to establish a dialogue on the condition that the rebels lay 
down their weapons. 
  In response,the guerrillas sent a brief message to the local 
television station rejecting any type of negotiation with the 
government and announcing that the armed movement will continue. 

</TEXT>

