<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salinas Asks Ombudsman To Ensure Human Rights </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0601015994 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0041 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0601015994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Elizabeth Diaz Otero from the "Vector 21" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari has reaffirmed 
that respect for the civilian population's human rights, along 
with gauarantees that allow media representatives to carry out 
their duties, is of foremost importance in the search for a 
solution to the conflict in Chiapas. 
  The president ordered the people responsible for 
organizations involved in operations in the Chiapas highlands to 
ensure this. The Mexican president on 5 January asked Jorge 
Madrazo Cuellar, president of the National Human Rights 
Commission, to visit Chiapas to correct any situation that might 
harm civil rights. The Mexican ombudsman headed for San 
Cristobal de las Casas on the afternoon of 5 January. 

</TEXT>

