<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuban Envoy Denies Havana Supplying Rebels Arms </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0601024194 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0144 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0601024194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Marcela Gutierrez for the "Vector 21" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The armed struggle is not the way to resolve the 
problems Mexico is facing, Cuban Ambassador to Mexico Jose 
Fernandez de Cossio Rodriguez has said. He added that the 
situtation in Chiapas does not justify an armed uprising. Let 
us listen to the statements of Fernandez de Cossio: 
  [Begin Fernandez de Cossio recording] The armed struggle, as 
many other ways of settling problems in some countries, is not a 
universal recipe. In the places in which armed struggles have 
been waged, they have been caused by a series of factors, which 
do not appear to be present in the case of Mexico. [end 
recording] 
  In an interview here at the Foreign Relations Secretariat, 
the Cuban diplomat rejected the possibility that the weapons 
used by rebels may come from that Caribbean island. He voiced 
his country's solidarity with the decisions of the Mexican 
Government to seek a peaceful solution to the armed clashes in 
southern Mexico. 

</TEXT>

