<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rizo Stresses Need "To Optimize" Work in Camaguey </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0501173994 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0501173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Julian Rizo, who is a member of the Politburo and 
first secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba in Camaguey 
Province, emphasized that encouraging efficiency, authority, and 
discipline constitute pillars for tackling the current phase of 
the work being done in Camaguey Province. Rizo said the 
watchword is to optimize. He insisted on the need to emphasize 
tasks such as self-sufficiency [in food], health, education, 
services, obtaining currency, sugar production, and others. 
  Rizo spoke before over 1,200 political and government 
leaders 
from Camaguey municipality and, in his speech, alluded to the 
impact on Cuba's socioeconomic development of the 
intensification of the Yankee blockade and the collapse of the 
socialist bloc. He called on those present to collaborate in a 
determined way to convert the current work phase into a concrete 
reality. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

