<H3> <TI>   Lazo Presides Over PNR 35th Anniversary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0601152594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0601152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Best wishes from the people and political and mass 
organizations were conveyed by Esteban Lazo, first secretary of 
the Communist Party of Cuba in Santiago de Cuba and Politburo 
member, during the ceremony commemorating the 35th anniversary 
of the National Revolutionary Police [PNR]. Lazo presided over 
the main ceremony in commemoration of this occasion. Several PNR 
troops were promoted to the ranks of officer and noncommissioned 
officer. Seals denoting years of vigilance and combativity and 
the 30th anniversary of the CDR [Committees for the Defense of 
the Revolution] were presented during the ceremony held in 
Santiago de Cuba. It was also learned that activities were held 
throughout Cuba by PNR troops and the population, and political 
and mass organizations sent their best wishes to the members of 
the PNR. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

