<H3> <TI>   Castro, Other Officials Meet With U.S. Visitors </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0601142194 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0601142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Commander in Chief Fidel Castro received, at the 
Palace of the Revolution, 110 U.S. professionals who have come 
to Havana on a trip sponsored by the Cuban Studies Center of New 
York in coordination with the Cuban Institute of Friendship with 
Peoples, ICAP. The group is made up of university professors, 
economists, lawyers, journalists, physicians, and other 
professionals. The U.S. visitors have also met with Ricardo 
Alarcon, president of the National Assembly of the People's 
Government; Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina; Carlos Lage, 
secretary of the Executive Committee of the Council of 
Ministers; and Abel Prieto, president of the National Union of 
Cuban Writers and Artists, UNEAC. 

</TEXT>

