<H3> <TI>   Council of State Gives Order to Prima Ballerina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0401224494 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 0100 GMT 
22 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> FL0401224494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Council of State of the Republic of Cuba, at the 
suggestion of Culture Minister Armando Hart, has presented the 
Juan Marinero Order to prima ballerina Alicia Alonso. The order 
was given in recognition of the significant accomplishments 
attained during her brilliant artistic career and her invaluable 
contribution to the development of culture on the occasion of 
the 45th anniversary of the Cuban Ballet. This was also a happy 
coincidence for Alonso who is celebrating her birthday today. 
Likewise, the National Culture award was presented to a group of 
artists and technicians of the Grand Theater of Havana who have 
dedicated their lives to this important artistic endeavor. 

</TEXT>

