<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jordan, Rizo Address Agricultural Challenges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0601145094 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0601145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Alfredo Jordan, who is a Politburo member and also 
minister of agriculture, said in Las Tunas that the main 
challenge before the more than 600,000 sector workers in Cuba is 
to increase production this year and progressively reduce the 
state subsidy to agriculture. Julian Rizo Alvarez, first 
secretary of the Communist Party of Cuba in Camaguey Province, 
at a meeting with rural leaders expressed the opinion that every 
Basic Cooperative Production Unit in cane agriculture should 
have a tractor and a plow with which to prepare the land. He 
explained that he defends this idea because plowing must be done 
rapidly for cane recovery. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
