<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNO Expels UDC, MDN, APC From Ranks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0501191794 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0501191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Eli Altamirano, coordinator of the National 
Opposition Union [UNO] Political Council, has confirmed that 
three other parties were expelled from this coalition. The three 
parties expelled from the anti-Sandinist coalition are: the 
Christian Democratic Union [UDC], the Nicaraguan Democratic 
Movement [MDN], and the Conservative Popular Alliance [APC] 
headed by Miriam Arguello Morales. The reason the UDC, APC, 
and MDN were kicked out of the UNO ranks was that they refused 
to sign a statement, which was signed by the other UNO parties, 
demanding a national constituent assembly. Radio Nicaragua has 
been unable to contact the leaders of the expelled parties in 
order to get their reaction. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

