<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Menem Calls Mexico's Salinas To Express `Support' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0501213594 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1822 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0501213594 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Buenos Aires, 5 Jan (NA) -- President Carlos 
Menem today expressed his support for his Mexican colleague, 
Carlos Salinas de Gortari, "in the name of the Argentine people" 
in view of the serious incidents carried out in Mexico by the 
brand-new Zapatista Army for National Liberation (EZLN). 
  This was reported by Media Secretary Raul Burzaco at the end 
of today's cabinet meeting in which the implementation of 
educational and social plans throughout the country and their 
projections were studied. [passage omitted] 
  Burzaco was charged with reporting the details of the first 
cabinet meeting of 1994, which was "complementary" to the last 
cabinet meeting of 1993. [passage omitted] 
  Burzaco reported that just after the end of the cabinet 
meeting, Menem called Salinas de Gortari "to express my support 
as a friend, as president, and in the name of the Argentine 
people in view of the subversive situation that is being 
experienced by your country." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

