<F P=100> Chile </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gen. Pinochet Visits Defense Minister-Designate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0701021294 Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional in Spanish 0000 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0701021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Santiago Television Nacional de Chile Imagen 
Internacional </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Army commander in chief, General Augusto 
Pinochet, today visited Defense Minister-designate Edmundo Perez 
Yoma in his home together with four major generals. The visit 
was qualified as a protocol visit. 
  Today at noon, Perez Yoma went to the office of 
President-elect Eduardo Frei Ruiz-Tagle on Hindemburg Street to 
inform him about his meeting with the Army commander. It was a 
cordial meeting, Perez Yoma said, adding that he told Pinochet 
of his intention to maintain extremely good relations with the 
military during the next administration. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Gen. Pinochet 
never 
paid a visit to Defense Minister Rojas. What do you think of 
this? 
  [Perez Yoma] I did not know that, and I greatly appreciate 
the fact that Gen. Pinochet, together with four other generals, 
visited me in my home and presented these major generals to me. 
So I am very happy about it. [end recording] 
  Perez Yoma was asked whether the visit was a demonstration 
of 
Gen. Pinochet's subordination to political power. 
  [Begin Perez Yoma recording] I think Gen. Pinochet has 
demonstrated he is willing to submit to the political power. I 
think his visit expresses his good intentions regarding this 
subject. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

