<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister on Possible New Terrorist Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0601171794 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0601171794 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Global TV News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Interior Minister Juan Briones Davila did not deny 
the existence of a small terrorist group in the country. He 
also announced the arrest of four alleged rebels accused of 
carrying out the attacks at the Lima Mayor's Office and the Air 
Force installations. 
  [Begin recording] [Briones] No, we cannot discount the 
possibility of another small group and -- I repeat -- a small 
group. We do recommend that they take the appropriate measures, 
because the terrorism law is very strict. I would not like 
anyone to claim later that we acted too drastically with them. 
At this time I think we should say -- and I would like to end 
with this -- that we will continue our counterterrorism 
operations. We want to finish this once and for all, arrest all 
those involved in the recent terrorist actions, and punish them 
with the full force of the law. We will keep working until we 
attain complete peace in the country. 
  [Unidentified reporter] Are any suspects under arrest? 
  [Briones] At this time we are still investigating. There 
have been a few arrests. 
  [Reporter] How many? 
  [Briones] We now have about four people in custody. They are 
important people within their organizations. We continue to 
investigate, and we expect to see some results soon. 
  [Reporter] Are these people members of Shining Path or the 
Tupac Amaru Revolutionary Movement? 
  [Briones] The people we have arrested are members of Shining 
Path. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

