  [Excerpt] Kingston, Jamaica, 6 Jan, CANA -- Jamaica's 
junior doctors who went on strike late Wednesday are to return 
to work, effective immediately. The doctors have agreed to end 
their strike following further assurances from government that 
anomalies between doctors and other public health sector workers 
will be dealt with. [passage omitted] 

