<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ambassador to Mexico Denies EZLN Links </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0701013594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0004 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0701013594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Ambassador to Mexico Jose Fernandez de Cossio 
Rodriguez has said that a strong, stable, and prosperous Mexico 
is important for the Cuban people. Fernandez de Cossio made 
this statement to the Mexican press when asked about the 
situation in Chiapas State. PRENSA LATINA reported that the 
Cuban diplomat in Mexico said that the Chiapas State incident is 
strictly a domestic matter and that the Cuban Government 
supports all efforts being made to find a peaceful solution to 
the problem. Regarding specific charges aimed at linking Cuba 
with the so-called Zapatist Army of National Liberation [EZLN], 
Fernandez de Cossio said that they are groundless. The 
ambassador said that those making these charges only want to 
cast a shadow on the relations between Mexico and Cuba, adding 
that, for the longest time, these relations have been based on 
the principle of non-intervention. 

</TEXT>

