<H3> <TI>   Chernobyl Children Arrive for Care </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0601195694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0601195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] One hundred forty children from Chernobyl arrived at 
Jose Marti International Airport today as part of the program of 
integrated care offered by our country. Over 13,000 Ukrainians, 
Russians, and Belarusians have been cared for over the past 
three years by the medical-recreational services in Tarara, east 
of the capital, where there is a joint facility, including a 
200-student primary school, for diabetic and asthmatic children. 

</TEXT>

