<F P=101> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troops on Alert Along Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0701025494 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2136 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0701025494 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Guatemala City, 6 Jan (ACAN-EFE) -- The 
Guatemalan Army today placed its troops along the Mexican border 
on alert after it confirmed the presence of insurgent Mexican 
columns within 800 meters of national territory. Army 
spokeswoman Major Edith Vargas told ACAN-EFE that the Military 
Command is coordinating surveillance along the border, which is 
divided into seven military zones, although it has not felt the 
need to send reinforcements. 
  On 1 January, the Zapatista National Liberation Army (EZLN) 
declared war on the Mexican Government in the southeastern state 
of Chiapas, where clashes have left more than 200 dead, 
according to various sources. Since yesterday, EZLN rebels have 
been present in the community of Guadalupe Tepeya, about 800 km 
from the Guatemalan border north of Huehuetenango Department. 
Security and defense in this area is under Military Zone No. 
19, but the border area is also being guarded by troops and 
detachments that are under commands [centrales] in the northern 
departments of Quiche and Alta Verapaz. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

