<F P=101> Costa Rica </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Expresses Solidarity With Mexico on Chiapas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0801040594 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0042 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0801040594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Jose, 7 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- Today Costa Rican 
President Rafael Angel Calderon expressed his solidarity with 
the Mexican Government, and he called on the rebel groups 
operating in several towns in the Mexican state of Chiapas to 
stop the violence. 
  The president said in a telephone call, "I expressed our 
broad and brotherly solidarity to Mexican President Carlos 
Salinas de Gortari, and today I want to take this opportunity to 
publicly reiterate it." 
  Calderon said that the violent actions in Chiapas are 
unjustified now that Salinas de Gortari "has made Mexico a 
nation of great economic and social development, the fruits of 
which are already being experienced by the people." Violence, 
he stressed, has never been a foundation for democratization 
processes or a permanent base for social achievements. 

</TEXT>

