<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   De Leon Accepts Resignation of Economy Minister Dominguez </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0901205694 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 6 Jan 94 
p95 </F>

<F P=103> PA0901205694 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Ramiro de Leon Carpio accepted yesterday 
afternoon the resignation of Economy Minister Fanny Dominguez de 
Estrada and named Guillermo Rodriguez Mahuad as acting minister. 
  It was officially announced last night that President de 
Leon 
decided to accept Estrada's resignation after studying the 
matter. She submitted her resignation in mid-November, shortly 
after replacing Cesar Alcides Soto Rodas. 
  Ms. Estrada resigned citing health reasons, but the 
government announced last night she will be named head of the 
Association of Nontraditional Products (Gexpront), where she 
performed a work public officials and private businessmen have 
described as successful. 
  Banker and exporter Eduardo Gonzalez Castillo is reportedly 
a 
strong contender to replace Estrada, although the possibility 
that Rodriguez may be confirmed has not been ruled out, given 
that he is also an expert in commerce and international 
businesses. 

</TEXT>

