<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Reports Heavy Fighting in North 22 Dec-5 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0701140894 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0701140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A large number of military activities have occurred 
in the northern part of the country between 22 December 1993 and 
5 January 1994, according to the Nicaraguan Army's public 
relations office. Eleven clashes occurred between 22 December 
and 5 January, between irregular groups and the EPS [Sandinist 
People's Army], in the northern zone of the country. The 
irregulars have sustained 30 casualties -- four dead, 10 
injured, and 16 prisoners. All are members of different groups, 
both recontras and recompas. Two civilians were injured, two 
kidnapped, and nine killed during that time. 

</TEXT>

