<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coast Guard Command Staff Members Listed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0801155094 Buenos Aires LA PRENSA in Spanish 5 Jan 94 
Section 1 p 6 </F>

<F P=103> PY0801155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires LA PRENSA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The National Coast Guard chief of staff, Prefect 
General Jorge Humberto Maggi, has joined the Argentine Naval 
Coast Guard top brass after the promotions to the top-ranking 
posts for officers of the institution were approved by the 
Executive Branch. 
  The new command is made up as follows: 

  -  Deputy chief of staff: Prefect General Jorge Arnoldo 
Gantiluomo; 
  -  Intelligence chief: Prefect General Carlos Justo 
Leyes; 
  -  Navigation safety police director: Prefect General 
Fortunato Cesar Benasulin; 
  -  Zonal Coast Guard chief: Prefect 
General Juan Marcos Redon; 
  -  Security and law enforcement police 
chief: Prefect General Raul Celear Dimarco; 
  -  Secretary general: 
Prefect General Juan Carlos Rinaldi; 
  -  Administration director: 
Prefect General Ruben Roberto Astiasaran. 

</TEXT>

