<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Colorado Party President Riquelme Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0701150894 Asuncion Radio Primero de Marzo in Spanish 1430 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0701150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion Radio Primero de Marzo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] We would like to reiterate that Blas N. Riquelme 
resigned today as president of the Colorado Party. The 
controversy between Riquelme and President Juan Carlos Wasmosy 
came to a conclusion today when the controversial politician and 
brewery owner resigned. 
  Riquelme's resignation was reported at the headquarters of 
the Colorado Party by Eugenio Sanabria Cantero, first vice 
president of the Colorado Party Executive Board, to whom 
Riquelme conveyed his decision to resign after a telephone 
conversation they held this morning. 
  According to the statutes of the Colorado Party, Sanabria 
Cantero automatically becomes the acting president of the 
Colorado Party. The party's executive board is holding a 
closed-door meeting to evaluate Riquelme's situation regarding 
his controversy with President Wasmosy. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

