<H3> <TI>   Duran-Ballen's Visit Postponed `Until Further Notice' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0701144194 Lima Global de Television Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0701144194 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima Global de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Global TV News" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpts] President Alberto Fujimori revealed today that 
Ecuadoran President Sixto Duran-Ballen's upcoming visit to Peru 
has been postponed until further notice. The head of state also 
referred to other issues during the various activities he 
carried out at the settlement of Huaycan. [passage omitted] 
  Shortly before concluding his tour, he briefly inspected the 
site where the local technological institute is being built. In 
his statements to the media Fujimori ruled out the possibility 
that Ecuadoran President Duran-Ballen's visit to our capital 
will take place on 20 January. 
  [Begin Fujimori recording] The date has not been officially 
coordinated at the Foreign Ministry level. In any case, it will 
not occur on 20 January -- but we are waiting for our Foreign 
Ministry to establish the most appropriate date. We are 
obviously waiting for this expectantly, to welcome the president 
of our brother country Ecuador with open arms, as he deserves. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

