<H3> <TI>   Robaina Visits Switzerland </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0701222394 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2032 GMT 
7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0701222394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina is currently 
visiting Switzerland, where he will spend the weekend and will 
meet with Swiss Foreign Affairs Secretary (Jacob Kellenberger). 
Cuban official sources have reported that Robaina has stopped 
over in Berne on his way to Africa and will take advantage of 
this stopover to meet with Swiss authorities and visit the 
capital city, particularly the Parliament. Robaina will leave 
Berne on Sunday. This is the second time Robaina has visited 
Switzerland; his first visit was in 1993 when he addressed the 
Social and Economic Council to explain the Cuban situation. At 
that time Robaina also met with Swiss authorities, UN officials 
in Geneva, Latin American ambassadors, and other ambassadors to 
the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

