<F P=102>  PA0801200494 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1800 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0801200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "NTC News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Manuel Camacho Solis, Mexican foreign secretary, 
will arrive in Colombia within hours to request emergency towers 
for an electric interconnection to the electric company in Santa 
Fe de Bogota. Both Mayor Jaime Castro and the national 
government have stated their willingness to help Mexico. 
  Colombia will lend the Mexican Government 25 electric towers 
to cooperate in the crisis in that country, given the partial 
destruction of its electric infrastructure by Zapatista 
guerrilla forces. 
  [Begin Energy Minister Guido Nule recording] We began 
immediately the process yesterday, and it should be complete by 
now, so we can send them in an airplane that will be directly 
sent from Mexico by them; in other words, those towers should be 
in Mexico this very day. [end recording] 
  Mayor Jaime Castro announced that municipal authorities will 
also join the international cooperation efforts. 
  [Begin Castro recording] It is an act of solidarity from 
Santa Fe de Bogota to the Mexican people. [end recording] 
  Mexican Foreign Minister Manuel Camacho Solis will arrive in 
Santa Fe de Bogota within hours to receive the Colombian aid and 
personally supervise its shipment to Mexico. 

</TEXT>

