<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Jose Ignacio Penagos in Medellin from the "NTC </F>
Newscast"] 
  [Text] The Mexican Government delegation--which is trying 
to resolve the electric power emergency in southern Mexico as a 
result of Zapatista National Liberation Army [EZLN] attacks--is 
in Medellin. Helped by executives of Electrical 
Inter-Connection, Inc. [ISA], they are seeking to establish 
contacts with private companies that can provide parts to the 
Mexican Federal Electricity Commission and to purchase an 
undetermined number of high-tension pylons. They have reached 
agreements with public enterprises of Medellin, the electric 
power companies of Santa Fe de Bogota and Cali, and with ISA. 
  [Begin Victor Manuel Ibarra, Mexican delegation member, 
recording] I am only coordinating certain administrative 
matters. [end recording] 
  Several members of the Mexican delegation have traveled to 
Cali. Meanwhile, other members are in Medellin with ISA Manager 
Diego Landizabal to meet with executives of the enterprises that 
can help resolve the Mexican electric power problem. 

