<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Center for Strategic Planning Created </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0801151694 Montevideo LA MANANA in Spanish 3 Jan 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> PY0801151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Montevideo LA MANANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The executive branch has ordered the creation of a 
Center for Advanced National Studies [Centro de Altos Estudios 
Nacionales] (Calen) with the purpose of training Armed Forces 
officers and civilians from both the public and private sectors 
in strategic planning and advising. 
  The objective of Calen is, among others, to increase 
knowledge of the true national situation within a regional, 
continental, and international context, through appropriate and 
modern methodologies. 
  This center will be in charge of the National Higher Studies 
Course established in 1986. The center will be headed by a 
director, who will be responsible to the Defense Ministry. It 
will also have an academic deputy director and a course director. 
  The post of director will be held by a general, and the 
deputy director will be a civilian (a professional with a 
university degree), or a graduate from Calen or from Esendena 
[National Defense and Security School]. 
  The executive branch will select the civilians who will 
study 
in Calen, who will be nominated by various organizations. The 
Defense Ministry and Armed Forces commanders will nominate 
officers to attend the courses. 
  Within the military career, the completion of these courses 
will be considered credit toward attaining an assignment. 
  According to the Defense Ministry the creation of this 
center 
will not represent any expense, because all the necessary 
resources are already available and need only be reallocated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-50866 </DOCNO>
