post of secretary general of his party, indicating that it is a 
role he has already fulfilled. He said Copei is a party that 
reaches agreements, and that is why it would endorse Caldera's 
request for support so he can have the political backing 
necessary to manage the country over the next five years. 
  [Begin Fernandez recording] The magnitude of the country's 
problems demands an effort of national understanding and unity. 
We must foster a climate to face the country's basic problems. 
[end recording] 
  Asked about the initiative to allow National Convergence to 
lead the Senate, he said it is one possibility that must be 
analyzed, adding that it is very possible it will become a 
reality. 

