<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Colombian Guerrillas Down National Guard Helicopter </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0701231194 Paris AFP in Spanish 2235 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0701231194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Caracas, Jan 7 (AFP) -- A Caracas radio station has 
reported that a helicopter of the militarized Venezuelan 
National Guard was downed in the Cutufi area near the Arauca 
River, close to the border with Colombia, after an attack by 
Colombian guerrillas. 
  Reports by Radio Caracas indicate that according to police 
sources in the area, a helicopter that was patrolling the border 
area was downed by a Colombian rebel commando. The crash had 
initially been attributed to technical problems. Two military 
policemen were injured. 
  Colombian rebels attacks, which have resulted in five deaths 
and the destruction of several military vehicles, have created 
friction between Bogota and Caracas over the past few months. 

</TEXT>

