<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bogota TV Reports Downing of Aircraft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0801004394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 0000 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0801004394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Another incident has exacerbated the already tense 
situation on the Colombian-Venezuelan border. The Guerrilla 
Coordinating Board downed a civilian helicopter from Venezuela 
that was transporting Venezuelan soldiers. The subversives also 
dynamited a vehicle transporting children in Aguazul, Casanare. 
  [Begin reporter Alvaro Ayala recording] The public order 
situation on the Colombian-Venezuelan border worsened today when 
ELN [Army of National Liberation] guerrillas opened fire on a 
civilian helicopter transporting Venezuelan soldiers. The 
incident occurred near the mouth of the Arauca River near 
Saravena. The two civilian pilots and four soldiers in the 
helicopter were seriously injured. They were subsequently 
rescued by the Venezuelan National Guard. 
  Meanwhile, the Guerrilla Coordinating Board dynamited a jeep 
of tourists coming from Boyaca as they were passing through 
Aguazul Municipality, Casanare. Two adults were killed and eight 
people, including seven children, were seriously injured. [end 
recording] 
  Regarding the case of the helicopter downed on the 
Colombian- 
Venezuelan border, we have just received another report from 
Arauca. According to that report, the Venezuelan helicopter 
landed in Colombian territory to pick up some peasants, and that 
is what led to the attack. The authorities are expected to 
issue a report on the events. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

