<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salinas Appoints Chiapas Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0901021294 Paris AFP in Spanish 0048 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0901021294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, Mexico, 8 Jan (AFP) -- 
President Carlos Salinas appointed a commission of Chiapas 
residents to "contribute" to restoring coexistence and normalcy 
to Chiapas," which for the past eight days has been shaken by 
clashes between the Army and guerrillas, the government reported 
on Saturday. 
  Social Development Secretary Carlos Rojas swore in the 
commission, which is made up of writer Eraclio Zepeda, 
anthropologist Andres Fabregas, and Institutional Revolutionary 
Party Senator Eduardo Robledo. 
  The commission "will have complete independence to evaluate 
the situation and the problems that need to be resolved as well 
as to make suggestions about options and actions to efficiently 
face the problems in the conflict areas," it was reported. 
  Rojas said the commission members' backgrounds "and their 
roots and identification with the people of Chiapas guarantee an 
objective reflection of the prevailing situation in the state 
and an intense dialogue with social organizations and 
communities in an effort to improve living conditions." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

