<H3> <TI>   PRD's Cardenas: Chiapas Affects Electoral Process </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0801212694 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
2000 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0801212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The 24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Cuauhtemoc Cardenas Solorzano, presidential 
candidate for the Party of the Democratic Revolution [PRD], 
expanded his position regarding the situation in Chiapas State 
and demanded new mechanisms to open up dialogue. 
  [Begin Cardenas recording] This conflict has already 
adversely affected the electoral process, regardless of its 
outcome. [end recording] 
  During a ceremony at a hotel in downtown Mexico City, Mr. 
Cardenas Solorzano accepted the support of the Broad Socialist 
Left Party [PAIS] for his presidential candidacy. The PRD 
candidate said the road leading to the solution of the Chiapas 
conflict is a negotiation and an immediate cease-fire. 

</TEXT>

