<H3> <TI>   PRD Leader Announces Peace Demonstration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0901172394 Mexico City Radio Mil Network in Spanish 1400 
GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0901172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio Mil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Report by Hector Ramos Aguilar; from "The City" newscast] 
  [Text] After stating his disagreement with the measures 
cited 
by Federal District Mayor Manuel Aguilera Gomez to protect 
Mexico City residents, Mexico City PRD [Party of the Democratic 
Revolution] leader (Rene Bejarano), who believes that the 
measures will restrict the people's freedom of movement, 
announced plans for a large peace demonstration. 
  [Begin (Bejarano) recording] We will march from the 
Revolution Monument to the Zocalo [Mexico City main square] on 
12, 13, or 14 January, and we will hold a large demonstration, 
which will probably be attended by our PRD presidential 
candidate, to demand peace in the country. [end recording] 
  (Bejarano) called the federal district mayor and political 
leaders to an urgent meeting to establish citizen protection 
measures that will not include the use of Army personnel to 
patrol the city. He said that far from calming the people, Army 
patrols will only alarm the public. 
  [Begin (Bejarano) recording] We believe the mayor should 
accept a meeting with political party presidents, social 
organizations, and city government personnel to reach an 
agreement that will impede [words indistinct] further in the 
political climate. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

