<H3> <TI>   Car Bomb in Mall Parking Lot; No Victims </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0801144494 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
1300 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0801144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mario Lopez; from the "Upon Awakening" newscast] </F>
  [Text] A car loaded with explosives blew up early Saturday 
morning, 8 January, in the parking lot of Plaza Universidad 
Mall, located between Universidad and Parroquia Streets, south 
of Mexico City. A report by the Mexico City Police indicated 
that a Nissan car, in which the explosives were allegedly 
placed, was destroyed. No victims were reported, although 
property damage was extensive. The parking lot and the mall were 
empty. Rene Monterrubio Lopez, general secretary of protection 
and highways, came to the site. 
  [Begin Monterrubio recording] Just one vehicle was damaged. 
All of the other vehicles inside the building are intact. [end 
recording] 
  The car bomb exploded entirely and damaged the central roof, 
part of the parking lot structure, and window panes. The police 
began an inquiry, although no group has claimed responsibility 
for the attack. 

</TEXT>

