<H3> <TI>   Caller Claims EZLN Responsible </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0801221994 Paris AFP in Spanish 2034 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0801221994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 8 Jan (AFP) -- An alleged spokesman of 
the Zapatista National Liberation Army [EZLN] told AFP over the 
telephone that the car bomb planted at a Mexico City shopping 
center early Saturday morning is "the first retaliation against 
Carlos Salinas de Gortari" for covering up for "his cousin, 
Patrocinio Gonzalez, the genocidal murderer of Indians." 
Gonzalez is currently the government secretary, 
  "This is an anonymous call, write this down quickly," a man 
with a faltering voice said before reading the message. 
  Early this morning a car bomb exploded up in an underground 
parking lot at the Plaza Universidad Shopping Center in southern 
Mexico City. There was extensive damage to some 20 shops, but 
no one was injured. 
  The man who phoned AFP gave no evidence that he was in fact 
a 
member of the EZLN. 

