<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guatemalan Charged for Chiapas Attacks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0901172294 Mexico City Radio Mil Network in Spanish 1400 
GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0901172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio Mil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Leonardo Rosas Gonzalez; from "The City" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Charged with the infliction of injuries, homicide, 
criminal association, and the use of exclusive Army regulation 
weapons, the Attorney General's Office [PGR] has requested that 
criminal proceedings be brought against Guatemalan Jesus Sanchez 
Galicia. 
  The Guatemalan has admitted to PGR officials that he had 
participated in armed attacks in Tecun and Ocosingo, Chiapas. 
He has confirmed that he had been arrested by Federal Judicial 
Police members at the highway checkpoint at the 
Catahashi-Chiapas crossroad, Tabasco State. Jose Sanchez 
Galicia has revealed that he is a native of Ticul Municipality 
in Guatemala, the country from where he received military 
training. Sanchez has been identified as one of the main 
commanders of the armed groups that are breaking the law in 
Chiapas. He said he is an expert in the handling of automatic 
weapons, pistols, revolvers, and rifles. He has been placed 
under the charge of the district criminal judge in Tuxtla 
Gutierrez, Chiapas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

