<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Continued EZLN Attacks on Garrison Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1001015694 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0106 GMT 10 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1001015694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 9 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- It was officially 
reported today that at least 97 are dead, an undetermined number 
are wounded, and 107 armed men have been captured by the Army 
since the beginning of the conflict in the southern Mexican 
state of Chiapas. 
  The National Defense Secretariat also stated in a communique 
that the armed group today, Sunday, fired for the eighth 
consecutive day against the headquarters of the 31st Military 
Zone, 10 km southeast of San Cristobal de Las Casas. 
  This time the members of the self-styled Zapatista National 
Liberation Army [EZLN], which on 1 January occupied several 
towns in Chiapas State, also cut the electricity supply to the 
region, stated the source. 
  According to the communique, 61 members of the armed group 
are dead and an undetermined number are wounded. As for the 
Army, three officers and six soldiers have died, and two 
officers and 27 soldiers have been wounded. 
  It has also been officially reported that 22 policemen and 
five civilians died during the first days of the clashes. 
  The military source reported that 107 members of the EZLN 
have been captured and that 145 firearms of different types and 
calibers, 17 grenades, 9,600 rounds of ammunition of different 
calibers, and 94 sticks of dynamite, among other materiel, have 
been seized from the EZLN. 
  On the ninth consecutive day of the conflict, the municipal 
capitals of Ocosingo, Las Margaritas, Altamirano, and San 
Cristobal de Las Casas, as well as other towns such as Chanal 
and Morelia, are under military protection. 
  The Army maintains checkpoints in the conflict areas to 
"protect the citizenry from the aggressors' attacks against 
vehicles" and to keep the armed group from stealing vehicles and 
using them in their activities. 
  The communique indicated that in towns such as San Cristobal 
de Las Casas, Ocosingo, and Altamirano, the Army is offering 
medical attention, distributing food, and providing attention to 
[words indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

