<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Publication: Wasmosy Receives `Orders' From Oviedo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1001154294 Asuncion NOTICIAS in Spanish 10 Jan 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> PY1001154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion NOTICIAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] "Army News," an official publication of the 
Paraguayan Army, says that engineer Juan Carlos Wasmosy, the 
president of the Republic and commander in chief of the Armed 
Forces, is following orders from Armed Forces generals over the 
appointment of Cavalry officers. 
  The December issue of "Army News" carries a report 
elaborating on the latest changes in the military field. Beside 
mentioning [Army Commander] General Lino Oviedo in most 
articles, the publication reports that Wasmosy received 
instructions over some appointments in the Cavalry divisions. 
  The publication notes that the president and commander in 
chief of the Paraguayan Armed Forces appointed the new 3d 
Cavalry Division chief of staff, "on the orders" of the Army, 
which is headed by Gen. Lino Cesar Oviedo, the Army commander. 
  The text is as follows: "Engineer Juan Carlos Wasmosy, in 
his 
capacity as commander in chief of the Paraguayan Armed Forces, 
appointed DEM [General Staff School graduate] Colonel Enrique 
Montiel G. as chief of staff of the 3d Cavalry Division on the 
orders of General Rodrigo Diaz Delmas, the 1st Army Corps 
Commander, through orders issued by Gen. Lino Oviedo, the 
Paraguayan Army commander ..." A facsimile of this report, 
which appears on page 7 of the December issue of "Army News," is 
published on this page. 
  In the aforementioned publication's center page, Gen. Oviedo 
is quoted as saying he will build "one school per year to save 
Paraguay from poverty." The publication did not specify, 
however, with what funds he will build schools. There is a 
picture of the general awarding medals to high school graduates 
in the interior of the country. 

</TEXT>

