<H3> <TI>   Deputy Denounces Government Threat To Take Over Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1001210694 Asuncion ULTIMA HORA in Spanish 10 Jan 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> PY1001210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion ULTIMA HORA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Ismael Echague [Colorado Party -- Concepcion] 
this morning denounced that "at approximately 2000 local time, 
on the eve of Blas N. Riquelme's resignation from office as 
Colorado Party president, we received a message from Government 
House to the effect that the [Colorado Party] Executive Board 
would be taken over and [Second Vice President Juan Manuel] Cano 
Melgarejo would be named party chairman unless Riquelme tendered 
his resignation." 
  Ecahgue, a member of Riquelme's faction within the party, 
further stated that one of the conditions for Riquelme's 
resignation -- imposed by Riquelme himself -- was that he would 
be replaced by Eugenio Sanabria Cantero, the party's first vice 
president. 
  Echague concluded by saying that "the pressure exerted from 
Government House was the main factor determining the former 
president's resignation, especially if one bears in mind that 
ministers and high-ranking government officials were already in 
favor of this proposal at that time." 

</TEXT>

