<F P=102>  FL1101022794 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1101022794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina is on an 
official visit to Ghana. Upon arrival, he was greeted by 
Ghanaian Foreign Minister Obed Asamoah. In Ghana the Cuban 
foreign minister begins his five-country tour that will include 
Angola, Zimbabwe, Zambia, and Namibia. During his 48-hour stay 
in Ghana, Foreign Minister Robaina will meet with Ghanaian 
President Jerry John Rawlings and other high-ranking Ghanaian 
officials. Robaina also will meet with members of various 
friendship organizations as well as with the Cuban ambassadors 
to Cape Verde, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Nigeria, Benin, and 
Burkina Faso. 

